com.ibm.team.scm.common
Interface IChange

public interface IChange

Represents a change (add, delete, modify) to a single versionable item. For versionable items, changes are implicitly understood as being relative to a context (the configuration) that determines which versionable items are included and what state each of them is in. Each versionable item in a change set will have only one IChange describing the change.

Note 1: There are points of similarity between IChangeSet/IChange and IUpdateReport/IItemUpdateReport. The former is used for long-term storage of change information in a change history. The latter is used for describing the outcome of an accept operation.

Note 2: It may be confusing that the states are also of type IVersionableHandle. The difference between a versionable and a versionable state is that a versionable state references a particular state of the versionable and has a state id.

Since:
0.5

NONE

static final int NONE
Kind constant indicating the change has equivalent "before" and "after" states. Both states are either both null, or both non-null with equivalent item and state identifiers. This may occur when a user resolves a conflict with "mine". The before state is the same as the after. The change is relevant because it represents what happened during the merge but nothing really happened.

See Also:
IChange.kind(), Constant Field Values

ADD

static final int ADD
Kind constant indicating the addition of a versionable item in the state given by IChange.afterState(). For this kind of change, the "after" state is never null, and the "before" state is always null.

See Also:
IChange.kind(), Constant Field Values

MODIFY

static final int MODIFY
Kind constant indicating the modification of a versionable item from the state given by IChange.beforeState()to the state given by IChange.afterState(). Both "before" and "after" states are for the same versionable item, and are both non- null and non-equal for this kind of change.

Method Detail

kind

int kind()
Returns the kind of change. The value is either IChange.NONE, IChange.ADD, IChange.DELETE or a bitwise OR of the following flags:
  • MODIFY
  • RENAME
  • REPARENT

Returns:
a valid change kind

item

IVersionableHandle item()
Returns the handle of the versionable item.

Returns:
the versionable item handle; never null

beforeState

IVersionableHandle beforeState()
Returns the "before" state of the versionable item, or null if the change is the addition of a versionable item to the configuration.

Always returns null for an addition. For a modification, returns non- null.

Returns:
the "before" state of the versionable item, or null if the change is an addition

mergeStates

java.util.List mergeStates()
Returns the additional states of the versionable item that were merged with the "before" state. Some of the elements may be null, indicating the merging of a deletion of the versionable item.

Even when the before state is null (an addition), the list of merge states may be non-empty indicating a merge with another history in which the item was already present (evil-twin).

Consider this list to be the proposed versions that were merged with the before state. The after state is the versionable after the merge has been completed. The state of the user's version (mine) before the merge is not recorded in this IChange. It can be found in the IChange of the previous IChangeSet state.

If the after state is the same as the latest merge state, the conflict was resolved by accepting the proposed version instead of resolving with mine or merging.

Returns:
the possibly empty list of merge states of the versionable item for a modification or deletion (element type: IVersionableHandle or null)

getMergeKind

int getMergeKind(IVersionableHandle mergeState)
Returns the change kind which describes the type of change between the supplied merge state and the after state.

Parameters:
mergeState - must be a valid merge state handle as produced from mergeStates; null is allowed if there is a null merge state handle.
Returns:
a valid change kind
See Also:
IChange.mergeStates()

afterState

IVersionableHandle afterState()
Returns the "after" state of the versionable item, or null if the change is the deletion of a versionable item from the configuration.

Always returns null for a deletion. For a modification or addition, always returns non-null.

Returns:
the "after" state of the versionable item, or null if the change is a deletion
